# Replit
.cache/
# The system-level /etc/.gitignore excludes the .local/ directory wholesale.
# We want to keep that exclusion in spirit (agent scratch, session plans,
# task notes should not be committed) but allow specific operational
# deliverables that happen to live under .local/ to be tracked.
#
# Git rule: a file under an excluded directory cannot be re-included via
# !pattern. So we (1) un-exclude the directory itself, (2) re-exclude its
# contents with .local/*, then (3) un-exclude the specific files we want.
!.local/
.local/*
# Track the beta-mode operational runbook (Task #46). It lives under
# .local/ per the task spec but is a real launch-ops deliverable that
# must be committed.
!.local/beta-mode-runbook.md
